\title{Intensionally pseudocontinuous [#{\mathcal{V}}-dcpo](axt-0021)}
\taxon{definition}
\date{2023-10-29}
\author{tom-de-jong}
\author{martin-escardo}

\def\UU{\mathcal{U}}
\def\VV{\mathcal{V}}
\def\WW{\mathcal{W}}

\p{
  A \em{pseudocontinuous} [#{\VV}-dcpo](axt-0021) is the analogue of the notion
  of an [intensionally continuous dcpo](axt-001K) in which the requirement of a
  specified directed [#{\VV}-family](axt-001F) is replaced by mere existence of
  such a directed family.
}
